<p><b>John Richard Pilger</b> (born 9 October 1939) is an <a href="/wiki/Australia" title="Australia">Australian</a> <a href="/wiki/Journalism" title="Journalism">journalist</a> and <a href="/wiki/Documentary_film" title="Documentary film">documentary</a> maker. One of only two to win Britain's Journalist of the Year Award twice, his documentaries have received academy awards in Britain and the US.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> Based in <a href="/wiki/London" title="London">London</a>, he is known for his polemical campaigning style: "Secretive power loathes journalists who do their job, who push back screens, peer behind façades, lift rocks. Opprobrium from on high is their badge of honour."</p>
